value.0: Shaundakul's Dogma: Spread the teachings of the Helping Hand by example. Work to promote him among traders, especially trailblazers who seek out new lands and new opportunities. Unearth and resanctify ancient shrines of Shaundakul. Ride the wind, and let it take you wherever it blows. Aid those in need, and trust in the Helping Hand. Seek out the riches of the earth and sea. Journey to distant horizons. Be the first to see the rising sun, the mountain peaks, the lush valleys. Let your footsteps fall where none have tread.

Years ago, Endir's Point was founded by a traveling Shaundakulite named Endir, though his last name has been lost to time. Endir came across the ore-rich coastline and surrounding hills while riding Shaundakul's wind.

He honoured the Windrider by building a monument to the Helping Hand, as is tradition upon discovering new lands. While quarrying for the needed stone north of the landing spot, he discovered ore-deposits. Endir saw this as a sign and decided to settle on this land, for he was certain that the wind brought him there for such a reason.

Over the months, Endir and his sailors established a meager colony as word spread of the rich ore-deposits. They began bringing in miners, Dwarves, hunters, fishermen and life slowly poured into the hamlet; mines were dug, a small dock was built, and a lighthouse constructed on a sea-cliff to establish some sort of trade route to provide for the infant settlement.
